Afghanistan Awarded $52 Million World Bank Grant for Resources

-- B y   J e s s e   R i s e b o r o u g h
-- 
2011-07-16T11:33:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-16/afghanistan-awarded-52-million-world-bank-grant-for-resources.html
Afghanistan ’s Ministry of Finance
was awarded a $52 million grant from the World Bank’s
International Development Association to support its efforts to
manage the country’s natural resources.  “Developing Afghanistan’s natural resources in an open,
transparent and efficient manner is a top priority in the
government’s agenda,” Omar Zakhilwal, Minister of Finance, said
today in an e-mailed statement. “The government remains
committed to ensuring the country’s rich mineral potential is
managed according to internationally accepted norms and
procedures for the benefit of the people of Afghanistan.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jesse Riseborough in London at 
 jriseborough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at   mharrison5@bloomberg.net  